on 12/20/00 7:13 AM, G Ramasubramani at grama@... wrote:

Paul,

       It is not a package problem as I am able to execute it using the
textui.TestRunner. The problem appears when I try to cast a particular
object as another Class. This casting goes through fine with the textui
flavour, but gives a problem if I use any other flavour TestRunner. It
appears that there are 2 class loaders at work here and hence the problem.
If no one has come across this earlier or no one knows a possible resolution
I might have to go through the TestRunner code - something which I don&#39;t
want to do :-)

thanks,
Rama

A non-loading graphical test runner is available -- in JUnit 3.2 and
earlier, junit.swingui.NonLoadingTestRunner will not reload classes.  Does
that runner show the problem?

It seems to me that I&#39;ve seen this before, and that the problem had to do,
as you say, with hanging on to a reference to a class from one classloader
and trying to cast to or from a class from another, although I can&#39;t
remember quite how.  It is true, I think, that even if ClassA extends
ClassB, ClassA from classloader 1 is incompatible with ClassB from
classloader 2.

---
